cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL 

The paper proposes a deep convolutional neural network (DCNN) for semantic segmentation of LiDAR scans, which is a computer vision task (cs.CV). The application of this network is for autonomous robot operation, which falls under robotics (cs.RO). The paper also proposes a Bayes filter-based method for making predictions temporally consistent, which involves probabilistic modeling and estimation (cs.LG). The use of a DCNN for semantic segmentation also involves machine learning (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL) techniques.
